text: Molokini is a crescent-shaped, submerged volcanic crater which forms a small islet located in ʻAlalākeiki Channel between the islands of Maui and Kahoolawe in Maui County in Hawaii. The islet has an area of . It is at its highest point, and is about west of Makena State Park and south of Maalaea Bay. ==References== Category:Islands of Hawaii
